# Pandas UDFs — vectorized via Arrow

## Columnar batches, not row-by-row

- Transfers data in **Apache Arrow** batches; you operate on a `pd.Series`
- NumPy/pandas vectorization applies; Arrow removes most serialization overhead
- **Dramatically faster** than a plain Python UDF

## Three flavors

- **Series → Series** *(default)* — most row-wise transformations
- **Iterator of Series** — **set up once** (load a model, open a DB) before the batches
- **`groupBy().applyInPandas(f, schema)`** — a full `pd.DataFrame` per group

Must leave the built-ins? Reach for a **Pandas UDF before a plain one.**
